Let's say you have a shadow node react prop like this:

```
[ReactProp("foo")]
public void SetFoo(string value)
{
    this.foo = value;
    MarkUpdated();
    Dirty();
}
```

This will trigger a call to `OnCollectExtraUpdates`, and you can shuttle properties between your shadow node and your native node. No problem.

But what about a situation like this?

```
[ReactProp("imageUri")]
public void SetImage(string uri)
{
	ImageLoader::loadAsync(uri, () => {
      MarkUpdated(); 
      Dirty();
    }   
}
```

In this case, by the time the loading callback fires, the layout update has already finished, and calling `MarkUpdated` or `Dirty` has no effect. Is there a way to force a complete layout update or `OnCollectExtraUpdates` on demand?
